The paper deals with the broadcast channel, which is a classic topic in information theory and falls under the umbrella of communication and networking. The paper specifically focuses on the impact of channel state information on the achievable degrees of freedom region, which is a core concept in information theory and falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the impact of feedback and feedback quality, which is a topic that falls under the categories of networking (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper proposes novel multi-phase broadcast schemes, which is a topic that falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of channel state information on the achievable performance, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer engineering (cs.CE).
